{"TopicId":154706,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Bring back the beta!","CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T23:25:46Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T23:25:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEver since the 1.1 update, version 0.90 has been absent from the KSP store. This may not sound like a big problem, and frankly\u00A0it\u0027s not, but (as far as I can tell) there\u0027s no reason not to bring it back. Some reasons for it, however, are an alternative physics system, infinigliders (which are very fun), no re-entry heating (which can be done in cheats and settings but it\u0027s on by default there), ion gliders, and just the ability to experience a piece of the past firsthand.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-12T16:38:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI kind of agree, but with a system simulair to the Minecraft Launcher. Just backup your stuff, select a game version, download and install it and then play!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-12T22:00:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf your going to do that, you might as well as add the alphas (.25) as well.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"REMD","CreatedById":111797,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-12T22:17:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell some people who cant play new version could welcome it too \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E(old pc (old version was playable, new is constanly crashing))\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-12T22:23:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah but which version? Squad released so many betas to ensure that 1.0 was free of bugs, had properly balanced aero and was well worthy of the 1.0 title, after all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-12T22:46:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222919627\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221484259795\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah but which version? Squad released so many betas to ensure that 1.0 was free of bugs, had properly balanced aero and was well worthy of the 1.0 title, after all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe you are mistaken, there was only 1 beta version, that being 0.90. If your referring to \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Ealpha\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E as I did above, then that\u0027s 0.7.3-0.25. There were updates to the \u003Cem\u003Erelease versions\u003C/em\u003E (1.0.0 and later), but they were while the game was in the \u0027released\u0027 status, and not beta. Hence why .90 was called \u0027Beta Than Ever\u0027.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-12T23:15:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222919627\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221484259795\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n52 minutes ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSquad released so many betas to ensure that \u003Cstrong\u003E1.0 was free of bugs\u003C/strong\u003E, had \u003Cstrong\u003Eproperly balanced aero\u003C/strong\u003E and was well \u003Cstrong\u003Eworthy of the 1.0 title\u003C/strong\u003E, after all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nL\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nO\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nL\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: also, yeah, there was only 1 Beta (0.90) and a whole lotta patches to fix the mess that was 1.0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-12T23:16:39Z\u0022 title=\u002201/12/2017 11:16  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 12, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Gaarst\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eddiew","CreatedById":127483,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-12T23:35:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222919627\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221484259795\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah but which version? Squad released so many betas to ensure that 1.0 was free of bugs, had properly balanced aero and was well worthy of the 1.0 title, after all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI call Poe!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNobody who went through the rapid aero changes of 1.0 - 1.0.4 could possibly make this statement with sincerity\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNearly had me though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ottothesilent","CreatedById":146852,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-12T23:43:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222919698\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221484264105\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI call Poe!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNobody who went through the rapid aero changes of 1.0 - 1.0.4 could possibly make this statement with sincerity\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNearly had me though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo be honest, 1.0.2 is my all-time favorite version\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-13T05:00:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222919648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221484261204\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103726\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ZooNamedGames\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, ZooNamedGames said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe you are mistaken, there was only 1 beta version, that being 0.90. If your referring to \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Ealpha\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E as I did above, then that\u0027s 0.7.3-0.25. There were updates to the \u003Cem\u003Erelease versions\u003C/em\u003E (1.0.0 and later), but they were while the game was in the \u0027released\u0027 status, and not beta. Hence why .90 was called \u0027Beta Than Ever\u0027.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might want to check your sarcasm-o-meter. It might need calibration...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-13T10:23:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222919935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221484283637\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might want to check your sarcasm-o-meter. It might need calibration...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI may be autistic and miss social cues but that original post had nothing sarcastic or otherwise rhetorical in nature. The way it was written to me suggested logical intent. Maybe consider rephrasing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jacke","CreatedById":103694,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-15T08:31:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222919698\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221484264105\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2017-01-12 at 4:35 PM, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNobody who went through the rapid aero changes of 1.0 - 1.0.4 could possibly make this statement with sincerity\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAero changed in KSP 0.90 and 1.0.5 as well.\u00A0 Seven major aero and thermal changes in a row was just too much for \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/74289-flowerchild/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002274289\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/74289-flowerchild/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@FlowerChild\u003C/a\u003E to balance one more time and the last version of BTSM released to date was for KSP 1.0.4.\u00A0 Which won\u0027t work properly under 1.0.5 (will be in places too easy or too hard).\u00A0 Can\u0027t really blame FC because those 1.0 subversion changes were at times crazy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-15T08:32:14Z\u0022 title=\u002201/15/2017 08:32  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 15, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Jacke\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gauga159","CreatedById":155603,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-15T09:22:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not go\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eeven further?\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0by adding the possiblility to play ksp v0.6.5, or every ksp version\u003Cs\u003E?\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rustedbloodline","CreatedById":165483,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-31T18:51:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou can download 0.90 from the Store\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont color=\u0022#272a34\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont face=\u0022Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont size=\u00222\u0022 style=\u0022font-size:10pt;\u0022\u003Einstead of left\u00A0clicking the icon to download the Zip file\u00A0right click the icon and paste the info into the address bar and change the numbers\u00A0at the end to a 0-90-0 and press enter\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}